	<abstract encodinganalog="520$a" label="Abstract:">Martha Hewitt was the wife of Dr. Harold Hewitt.  Dr. Hewitt was a professor of chemistry and Dean of the School of Pharmacy at the University of Connecticut from 1947 until his retirement in February 1972.  The collection contains a small amount of correspondence from Martha Hewitt to her family while traveling in Europe, documentation for her application to the DAR and other random personal papers.  The majority of the photographs are of Mrs. Hewitt's family, although there are some of Dr. Hewitt.</abstract>

	<unitid encodinganalog="099" label="Identification:" countrycode="us" 
