<bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Biography</head>
	<p><persname>Harold G. Hewitt</persname> received his degrees from the <corpname>University of Wisconsin</corpname> (B.S. 1923, M.S. 1925, Ph.D. 1926). In 1926, he married <persname>Martha Alexander</persname> and the couple moved to <geogname>Buffalo, NY</geogname>, where Harold had received an appointment to the faculty at the <corpname>University of Buffalo</corpname> as head of the Division of Chemistry in the School of Pharmacy.  In 1947, <persname>Harold G. Hewitt</persname> was selected by President <persname>Albert N. Jorgensen</persname> to fill the office of Dean of the School of Pharmacy (then located in New Haven) at the <corpname>University of Connecticut</corpname>.  Dr. Hewitt served as Dean until 1969 and retired from the University in 1972. While at the University of Connecticut, the Hewitts were close friends of Geraldine and Charles Waring.  The Warings had arrived in <geogname>Connecticut</geogname> the year before and Charles and Harold shared a similar background in Chemistry.</p>

<p><persname>Harold Hewitt</persname> died in the Spring of 1980.  Mrs. Hewitt died sometime in the 1980s.  <persname>Geraldine Waring</persname> was the executrix for <persname>Martha Hewitt</persname>'s estate.</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Contents</head>
	<p>The collection contains a small amount of correspondence from <persname>Martha Hewitt</persname> to her family while traveling in <geogname>Europe</geogname>, documentation for her application to the <corpname>DAR</corpname> and other random personal papers.  The collection also includes personal, family and professional activity (of <persname>Harold Hewitt</persname>) photographs.</p>
</scopecontent>

